AB  - Bayesian and sampling distributions of the mean squared errors of forecast (MSEF) are obtained using a new derivation of the distribution of a quadratic form in normal variates. The posterior mean of the MSEF is used as a criterion for model selections. Using sampling experiments we compare the Bayesian MSEF criterion with the AIC, Efron's confidence interval, the N, J, and encompassing tests. The Bayesian MSEF criterion tends to outperform the other criteria.
