UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769190029D
AB  - The problem of finding grouping bounds for a general class of inequality measures is examined under alternative assumptions about the presentation of the data: where the data are in grouped form with all interval boundaries and all interval means known, where the interval means are unknown but the population mean is known, and where the topmost interval boundary is unknown. The problems of existence and uniqueness of the bounds, the ‘integer problem’ for small populations, the relationship between different bounds and of computational algorithms are all examined.
